data.title: Saudi Arabia's weight loss market expected to reach $2.7 billion by 2033 due to obesity rates and government efforts - ResearchAndMarkets.com.
data.description: A report on the "Saudi Arabia Weight Loss Market by Diet 2025-2033" has been included in ResearchAndMarkets.com's offerings. The market in Saudi Arabia is expected to experience substantial growth, increasing from USD 1.6 Billion in 2024 to USD 2.7 Billion by 2033, indicating a Compound Annual Growth Rate (CAGR) of 5.68% between 2025-2033. This growth is fueled by the escalating rates of obesity, attributed to lifestyle shifts due to urbanization and the rise in income from oil reserves in the region. Factors such as the adoption of Western dietary habits and a decrease in physical activities also contribute to this trend.

data.title: Nasdaq drops as Meta and Microsoft decline, Cathie Wood stock dives. Chipotle sinks. Dow Jones rises.
data.description: Today, major indexes had mixed results in the stock market. The Dow Jones index experienced an increase, while the Nasdaq saw a decline. Meta stock took a significant plunge, contributing to the Nasdaq's drop. In addition, Chipotle stock also faced a decline. Meta and Microsoft were among the key companies impacting the market's performance. Notably, Cathie Wood's stock also experienced a notable dive. Overall, it was a dynamic day in the market with various significant movements in key stocks and indexes.

data.title: Carvana stock falls after mixed Q3 results: EPS $1.03 (missed estimates of $1.24), sales $5.64B, sold 155,941 units (44% YoY increase).
data.description: Carvana Co. (NYSE: CVNA) stocks are down after releasing their third-quarter financial results which were a mixed bag. The company faced a downturn in the market due to negative sentiment. For the third quarter, Carvana reported earnings per share of $1.03, falling short of the expected $1.24 as per Benzinga Pro. Despite this, the company surpassed sales expectations with total sales amounting to $5.64 billion instead of the anticipated $5.06 billion. In the same quarter, Carvana managed to sell 155,941 retail units, marking a significant 44% increase from the previous year, leading to a 55% year-over-year growth in total revenue. More details are accessible via Benzinga.com.

data.title: Google's Q3 results impress with $102.4 billion revenue, $35 billion net income, $2.87 EPS. Stock climbing. Analysts excited about AI momentum.
data.description: Alphabet, Inc. reported impressive Q3 results, surpassing expectations with total revenue reaching $102.4 billion â€“ the first quarter crossing $100 billion. Net income surged 33% to nearly $35 billion, and earnings per share rose to $2.87, a 35% jump. Google Cloud revenue increased by 34% to $15.16 billion, Search revenue went up by 14.5% to $56.57 billion, and YouTube ad revenue grew 15% to $10.26 billion. Analysts reacted positively, with Canaccord Genuity raising Alphabet's price target to $330, noting the company's focus on AI investments and innovative developments benefiting various business lines.

data.title: Satya Nadella redefines Microsoft's AI as a 'Token Factory,' boasting planet-scale efficiency. Company's AI data centers power GPT-5 training and Copilot queries, not reliant on single versions of Nvidia for all gigawatts.  Find full story on Benzinga.com.
data.description: In a recent earnings call, Satya Nadella presented a new metaphor for Microsoft Corp's (NASDAQ: MSFT) AI empire, referring to it as a "planet-scale token factory". This term describes the company's expansive global network of AI data centers, highlighting the efficiency of their operations. Nadella emphasized the continuous modernization of Microsoft's AI infrastructure, which supports various tasks such as GPT-5 training and Copilot queries. Unlike a singular vendor approach, Nadella explained that Microsoft's infrastructure is diversified for optimized performance. Investors can monitor MSFT stock performance closely. For more details, the full report is accessible on Benzinga.com.

data.title: UPMC Children's Hospital Foundation adds three new Trustees. Largest campaign nears completion.
data.description: In recent news from Pittsburgh on October 30, 2025, the UPMC Children's Hospital Foundation Board of Trustees have appointed three new members to their board. The new Trustees are Gina Astorino, Lara Patrinos Bentz, and Christopher (Chris) S. McElroy. This announcement comes as the Foundation approaches the conclusion of its largest campaign yet.

data.title: Merck beats earnings estimates with $2.58 EPS, $17.28B sales, considering larger deals, pharma segment at $15.61B.
data.description: Merck & Co., Inc. (MRK) experienced a tumultuous trading day post its Q3 earnings report and revised fiscal 2025 forecast. The pharmaceutical giant posted adjusted EPS of $2.58, exceeding the expected $2.35 and a notable increase from the previous year's $1.57. With reported sales of $17.28 billion, up 4% from last year, Merck outperformed analyst predictions of $16.96 billion. The pharmaceutical sector saw sales totaling $15.61 billion, a 4% increase driven by strong performances in oncology, cardiovascular, and diabetes. The company's new cancer therapy combo demonstrated superiority in the renal cancer segment. For more details, refer to the complete article on Benzinga.com.

data.title: Cardinal Health Inc. rallied on strong Q1 2026 results, with adjusted earnings of $2.55/share, sales up 22% to $64.01B.
data.description: Cardinal Health Inc., listed on NYSE as CAH, experienced a significant rise in stock value following a successful first-quarter report for 2026. The company recorded adjusted earnings of $2.55 per share, well above the anticipated $2.18, indicating a strong performance. Sales figures also displayed noteworthy growth, with a 22% year-over-year increase to $64.01 billion, surpassing the expected $59.19 billion. Adjusted operating earnings saw a considerable 37% rise, reaching $857 million. Particularly, the Pharmaceutical and Specialty Solutions segment saw a 23% revenue jump to $59.2 billion, fueled by increased sales in brand and specialty pharmaceuticals to both new and existing clients. For further details, visit the full story on Benzinga.com.

data.title: KBRA assigns ratings to auto loan securitization by First Investors Auto Owner Trust 2025-1 for Stellantis Financial Services.
data.description: In New York, KBRA has assigned preliminary ratings to six classes of notes from First Investors Auto Owner Trust 2025-1 (FIAOT 2025-1), an asset-backed securitization backed by auto loans. This marks the first term ABS securitization in 2025 for Stellantis Financial Services, Inc., also known as First Investors Financial Services (SFS), and the fourth since being acquired by Stellantis N.V. in 2021. FIAOT 2025-1 will issue a total of six classes of notes.

data.title: Svante marks 18 years in carbon management with historic milestones in 2025, including a commercial manufacturing facility.
data.description: In Vancouver, British Columbia, Svante Technologies Inc. (Svante), a prominent player in carbon capture and removal solutions, commemorates its 18th anniversary this month. Over the years, Svante has been at the forefront of developing industrial carbon management technology. The past year has been particularly significant for the company, characterized by groundbreaking innovation, key partnerships, and the launch of the world's inaugural commercial manufacturing plant for solid sorbent-based carbon capture.
